begin
reserve i for Nat;
reserve j for Nat;
theorem
( i * j ) = ( ( i lcm j ) * ( i gcd j ) )
proof
A1: ((i <> ( 0 ) & j <> ( 0 )) implies ( i * j ) = ( ( i lcm j ) * ( i gcd j ) ))
proof
assume that
A2: i <> ( 0 )
and
A3: j <> ( 0 );
A4: (i divides i implies i divides ( i * j )) by CKB14:1;
(j divides j implies j divides ( j * i )) by CKB14:1;
then ( i lcm j ) divides ( i * j ) by A4,CKB17:def 1;
then consider c being Nat such that A5: ( i * j ) = ( ( i lcm j ) * c ) by CKB7:def 1;
A6: i divides ( i lcm j ) by CKB17:def 1;
A7: j divides ( i lcm j ) by CKB17:def 1;
consider d being Nat such that A8: ( i lcm j ) = ( i * d ) by A6,CKB7:def 1;
consider e being Nat such that A9: ( i lcm j ) = ( j * e ) by A7,CKB7:def 1;
( i * j ) = ( i * ( c * d ) ) by A5,A8;
then A10: j = ( c * d ) by A2,XCMPLX_1:5;
( i * j ) = ( j * ( c * e ) ) by A5,A9;
then i = ( c * e ) by A3,XCMPLX_1:5;
then A11: c divides i by CKB7:def 1;
A12: c divides j by A10,CKB7:def 1;
(for f being Nat holds ((f divides i & f divides j) implies f divides c))
proof
let f being Nat;
assume that
A13: f divides i
and
A14: f divides j;
consider g being Nat such that A15: i = ( f * g ) by A13,CKB7:def 1;
consider h being Nat such that A16: j = ( f * h ) by A14,CKB7:def 1;
A17: ( j * g ) = ( ( g * h ) * f ) by A16;
( i * h ) = ( ( g * h ) * f ) by A15;
then A18: i divides ( ( g * h ) * f ) by CKB7:def 1;
j divides ( ( g * h ) * f ) by A17,CKB7:def 1;
then ( i lcm j ) divides ( ( g * h ) * f ) by A18,CKB17:def 1;
then consider z being Nat such that A19: ( ( g * h ) * f ) = ( ( i lcm j ) * z ) by CKB7:def 1;
A20: ( c * ( i lcm j ) ) = ( ( g * ( h * f ) ) * f ) by A5,A15,A16
.= ( ( ( i lcm j ) * z ) * f ) by A19
.= ( ( z * f ) * ( i lcm j ) );
( i lcm j ) <> ( 0 ) by A2,A3,INT_2:4;
then c = ( f * z ) by A20,XCMPLX_1:5;
hence thesis by CKB7:def 1;
end;
hence thesis by A5,A11,A12,CKB19:def 1;
end;
((i = ( 0 ) or j = ( 0 )) implies ( i * j ) = ( ( i lcm j ) * ( i gcd j ) ))
proof
assume A21: (i = ( 0 ) or j = ( 0 ));
then ( i * j ) = ( ( 0 ) * ( i gcd j ) )
.= ( ( i lcm j ) * ( i gcd j ) ) by A21,INT_2:4;
hence thesis;
end;
hence thesis by A1;
end;
